			<div class="content" id="post-content-3571059">
									

<blockquote>
<p>I feel this is redundant and should be deleted since it already exists.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I think you lack knowledge of what's going on here. There is no rule that there must only be one storyline for every plot thread. There can be multiple stories that account for Fuller's departure from the circus, and they can contradict for all one cares. So long the audience likes it and the rating is favourable, they have a right to exist.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Have you read all the Circus tales?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Based on the author's notes for the various Tales in the series and my interaction with him during critique, I can assure you that DrChandra has knowledge of articles featuring Herman Fuller.</p>
<p>Perhaps you would like to do your background checks before you make such insinuations?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Cause their is already a circus hub.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>That hub is the GoI hub, which is effectively just a place for all Herman Fuller articles to be linked from. This hub is specifically for a Tale Series, featuring a specific storyline. They can co-exist together perfectly fine.</p>

